{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"agent_message","text":"The failure is more subtle than a missing checked-in entry. `ReflectUtils` first calls `Class.forName(\"[Lchar;\")`, which is an invalid intermediate name for a primitive array, and native-image’s exact-metadata check trips on that first lookup before CGLIB falls back to the valid primitive-array form. I’m looking for an existing repo pattern for this kind of fallback-heavy `Class.forName` sequence before I change anything else."}}
