{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve found the likely mechanism: GraalVM exposes `RuntimeReflection.registerClassLookup(String)`, which is specifically meant to allow `Class.forName(String)` to return the class or a normal `ClassNotFoundException` at run time for a given lookup name. That fits CGLIB’s invalid intermediate lookup much better than JSON metadata does."}}
